# SEO Optimization Rules

## 2025 SEO Best Practices Applied
Based on latest SEO trends focusing on user intent, page experience, and function-first design.

## Page Structure Priority
1. **Function First**: Main AI tools on first screen (immediate value)
2. **SEO Content Second**: Features, About, FAQ moved to bottom
3. **No Hero Bloat**: Eliminate lengthy marketing copy from top fold
4. **Direct Action**: Users can immediately start generating/editing images

## User Intent Optimization
- **Match Search Intent**: "AI image generator" should lead to actual generator tool
- **Minimize Bounce Rate**: Provide immediate functionality, not just information
- **Increase Dwell Time**: Engaging tools that users actually use
- **User Signals**: Focus on metrics that indicate user satisfaction

## Content Strategy
```tsx
// ✅ SEO content placement (bottom of page)
<main>
  {/* Main Function - First Screen */}
  <section className="function-first">
    <ImageGenerator />
    <ImageEditor />
  </section>
  
  {/* SEO Content - Bottom sections */}
  <SEOContent />
</main>
```

## Meta Information Implementation
```tsx
// ✅ Structured data for WebApplication
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "DreamfinityX",
  "description": "AI-powered image generation and editing platform",
  "url": "https://dreamfinityx.com",
  "applicationCategory": "DesignApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Any",
  "offers": {
    "@type": "Offer",
    "price": "0"
  }
}
</script>
```

## Page Performance (Core Web Vitals)
- **Fast Loading**: Simplified design improves LCP
- **Reduced Layout Shift**: Consistent, compact components
- **Mobile Optimization**: Responsive design with touch-friendly elements
- **Clean Code**: Minimal dependencies, optimized images

## Content Guidelines
- **Keyword Natural Integration**: "AI image generation", "image editing"
- **Technical Terms**: "GPT-image-1", "Azure OpenAI", "text-to-image"
- **User-Focused Language**: How-to guides, practical benefits
- **Original Content**: Unique insights, not AI-generated fluff

## SEO Content Sections
1. **Features Section**: List key capabilities
2. **About Section**: Technology and value proposition
3. **FAQ Section**: Common questions and answers
4. **Technical Section**: AI model and capabilities

## E-E-A-T (Experience, Expertise, Authority, Trust)
- **Experience**: Show actual product functionality first
- **Expertise**: Reference Azure OpenAI and GPT-image-1 technology
- **Authority**: Professional design and reliable functionality
- **Trust**: Clear error handling, consistent user experience

## Mobile-First Indexing
- All components must be mobile-responsive
- Touch-friendly button sizes (minimum 44px)
- Readable text without zooming
- Fast mobile performance

## Content Freshness
- Keep FAQ and features up to date
- Maintain current technology references
- Regular content audits for accuracy

## Internal Linking Strategy
- Link between related features
- Clear navigation structure
- Breadcrumbs for complex pages
- Contextual links in content

